#originalStanceText=Yes
#originalTopic=Debate:_DC_handgun_ban
The social harm related to firearms outweighs any social benefits from possessing firearms It is empirically proven that the numbers of victims from gun related  attacks or incidents far outweigh the number of instances when arms were used for self protection.This warrants the argument that the costs incurred on society through the usage of arms are higher the the benefits the possession of arms for self defense brings
